{
    "publish_date": "2014-01-07T16:04:45.000Z", 
    "score": 0.00015860852055316445, 
    "video_length": "PT5M3S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Picture warm, gooey cookies,", 
            "dur": "2.252", 
            "start": "6.825"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "crunchy candies, velvety cakes,", 
            "dur": "2.951", 
            "start": "9.101"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "waffle cones piled high with ice cream.", 
            "dur": "2.594", 
            "start": "12.076"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Is your mouth watering?", 
            "dur": "1.953", 
            "start": "14.693"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Are you craving dessert?", 
            "dur": "1.197", 
            "start": "16.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Why?", 
            "dur": "1.031", 
            "start": "17.891"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What happens in the brain\nthat makes sugary foods so hard to resist?", 
            "dur": "4.73", 
            "start": "18.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sugar is a general term\nused to describe a class of molecules", 
            "dur": "3.389", 
            "start": "23.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "called carbohydrates,", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "27.113"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and it&#39;s found in a wide variety\nof food and drink.", 
            "dur": "2.827", 
            "start": "28.427"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just check the labels\non sweet products you buy.", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "31.278"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Glucose, fructose, sucrose,", 
            "dur": "2.468", 
            "start": "34.442"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "maltose, lactose, dextrose, and starch", 
            "dur": "2.849", 
            "start": "36.934"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are all forms of sugar.", 
            "dur": "1.955", 
            "start": "39.807"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So are high-fructose corn syrup,", 
            "dur": "1.931", 
            "start": "41.786"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fruit juice, raw sugar, and honey.", 
            "dur": "2.529", 
            "start": "43.741"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And sugar isn&#39;t just\nin candies and desserts,", 
            "dur": "2.929", 
            "start": "46.709"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s also added to tomato sauce,", 
            "dur": "1.524", 
            "start": "49.662"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "yogurt, dried fruit,\nflavored waters, or granola bars.", 
            "dur": "4.488", 
            "start": "51.188"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Since sugar is everywhere,\nit&#39;s important to understand", 
            "dur": "2.963", 
            "start": "55.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how it affects the brain.", 
            "dur": "1.195", 
            "start": "58.687"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What happens when sugar hits your tongue?", 
            "dur": "2.345", 
            "start": "59.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And does eating a little bit of sugar\nmake you crave more?", 
            "dur": "2.931", 
            "start": "62.275"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You take a bite of cereal.", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "65.753"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The sugars it contains activate\nthe sweet-taste receptors,", 
            "dur": "3.157", 
            "start": "67.347"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "part of the taste buds on the tongue.", 
            "dur": "2.218", 
            "start": "70.528"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These receptors send a signal\nup to the brain stem,", 
            "dur": "2.977", 
            "start": "72.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and from there, it forks off\ninto many areas of the forebrain,", 
            "dur": "3.466", 
            "start": "75.771"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one of which is the cerebral cortex.", 
            "dur": "2.528", 
            "start": "79.261"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Different sections of the cerebral cortex\nprocess different tastes:", 
            "dur": "4.17", 
            "start": "81.813"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bitter, salty, umami,", 
            "dur": "1.964", 
            "start": "86.007"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and, in our case, sweet.", 
            "dur": "1.804", 
            "start": "87.995"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From here, the signal activates\nthe brain&#39;s reward system.", 
            "dur": "3.593", 
            "start": "89.823"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This reward system is a series\nof electrical and chemical pathways", 
            "dur": "3.661", 
            "start": "93.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "across several different\nregions of the brain.", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "97.125"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s a complicated network,", 
            "dur": "1.286", 
            "start": "99.749"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it helps answer a single,\nsubconscious question:", 
            "dur": "3.425", 
            "start": "101.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "should I do that again?", 
            "dur": "1.345", 
            "start": "104.508"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That warm, fuzzy feeling you get\nwhen you taste Grandma&#39;s chocolate cake?", 
            "dur": "3.6", 
            "start": "105.877"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s your reward system saying,", 
            "dur": "1.879", 
            "start": "109.501"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Mmm, yes!&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.512", 
            "start": "111.404"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s not just activated by food.", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "112.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Socializing, sexual behavior, and drugs", 
            "dur": "2.286", 
            "start": "115.297"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are just a few examples\nof things and experiences", 
            "dur": "3.103", 
            "start": "117.607"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that also activate the reward system.", 
            "dur": "2.543", 
            "start": "120.734"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But overactivating this reward system\nkickstarts a series of unfortunate events:", 
            "dur": "5.344", 
            "start": "123.301"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "loss of control, craving,\nand increased tolerance to sugar.", 
            "dur": "3.631", 
            "start": "128.669"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s get back to our bite of cereal.", 
            "dur": "2.073", 
            "start": "133.158"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It travels down into your stomach\nand eventually into your gut.", 
            "dur": "3.633", 
            "start": "135.255"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And guess what?", 
            "dur": "1.013", 
            "start": "138.912"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There are sugar receptors here, too.", 
            "dur": "2.407", 
            "start": "139.949"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They are not taste buds,\nbut they do send signals", 
            "dur": "2.351", 
            "start": "142.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "telling your brain that you&#39;re full", 
            "dur": "1.808", 
            "start": "144.755"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or that your body should\nproduce more insulin", 
            "dur": "2.143", 
            "start": "146.587"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to deal with the extra sugar\nyou&#39;re eating.", 
            "dur": "2.225", 
            "start": "148.754"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The major currency\nof our reward system is dopamine,", 
            "dur": "2.943", 
            "start": "151.596"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an important chemical or neurotransmitter.", 
            "dur": "2.566", 
            "start": "154.563"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There are many dopamine\nreceptors in the forebrain,", 
            "dur": "2.507", 
            "start": "157.153"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but they&#39;re not evenly distributed.", 
            "dur": "2.132", 
            "start": "159.684"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Certain areas contain dense\nclusters of receptors,", 
            "dur": "2.784", 
            "start": "161.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and these dopamine hot spots\nare a part of our reward system.", 
            "dur": "3.663", 
            "start": "164.648"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Drugs like alcohol, nicotine, or heroin", 
            "dur": "2.651", 
            "start": "168.898"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "send dopamine into overdrive,", 
            "dur": "1.769", 
            "start": "171.573"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "leading some people\nto constantly seek that high,", 
            "dur": "3.059", 
            "start": "173.366"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in other words, to be addicted.", 
            "dur": "1.721", 
            "start": "176.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sugar also causes dopamine to be released,\nthough not as violently as drugs.", 
            "dur": "4.887", 
            "start": "178.645"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And sugar is rare\namong dopamine-inducing foods.", 
            "dur": "3.109", 
            "start": "183.556"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Broccoli, for example, has no effect,", 
            "dur": "1.939", 
            "start": "186.689"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which probably explains", 
            "dur": "1.436", 
            "start": "188.652"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "why it&#39;s so hard to get\nkids to eat their veggies.", 
            "dur": "2.701", 
            "start": "190.112"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Speaking of healthy foods,", 
            "dur": "1.556", 
            "start": "193.295"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let&#39;s say you&#39;re hungry\nand decide to eat a balanced meal.", 
            "dur": "2.815", 
            "start": "194.875"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You do, and dopamine levels spike\nin the reward system hot spots.", 
            "dur": "3.611", 
            "start": "197.714"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But if you eat that same dish\nmany days in a row,", 
            "dur": "3.357", 
            "start": "201.349"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "dopamine levels will spike less and less,\neventually leveling out.", 
            "dur": "4.244", 
            "start": "204.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s because when it comes to food,", 
            "dur": "1.762", 
            "start": "208.998"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the brain evolved to pay special attention\nto new or different tastes.", 
            "dur": "4.147", 
            "start": "210.784"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Why?", 
            "dur": "1.106", 
            "start": "214.955"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two reasons:", 
            "dur": "1.16", 
            "start": "216.085"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "first, to detect food that&#39;s gone bad.", 
            "dur": "2.516", 
            "start": "217.269"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And second, because the more variety\nwe have in our diet,", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "219.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the more likely we are\nto get all the nutrients we need.", 
            "dur": "3.099", 
            "start": "222.753"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To keep that variety up,", 
            "dur": "1.351", 
            "start": "225.876"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we need to be able\nto recognize a new food,", 
            "dur": "2.388", 
            "start": "227.251"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and more importantly, we need\nto want to keep eating new foods.", 
            "dur": "3.857", 
            "start": "229.663"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s why the dopamine levels off\nwhen a food becomes boring.", 
            "dur": "3.799", 
            "start": "233.544"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, back to that meal.", 
            "dur": "1.575", 
            "start": "237.367"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What happens if in place\nof the healthy, balanced dish,", 
            "dur": "3.102", 
            "start": "238.966"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you eat sugar-rich food instead?", 
            "dur": "2.191", 
            "start": "242.092"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you rarely eat sugar\nor don&#39;t eat much at a time,", 
            "dur": "3.008", 
            "start": "244.307"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the effect is similar\nto that of the balanced meal.", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "247.339"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But if you eat too much,\nthe dopamine response does not level out.", 
            "dur": "3.729", 
            "start": "249.973"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In other words, eating lots of sugar\nwill continue to feel rewarding.", 
            "dur": "3.995", 
            "start": "253.726"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In this way, sugar behaves\na little bit like a drug.", 
            "dur": "3.384", 
            "start": "257.745"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s one reason people seem\nto be hooked on sugary foods.", 
            "dur": "3.444", 
            "start": "261.153"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, think back to all those\ndifferent kinds of sugar.", 
            "dur": "2.892", 
            "start": "264.621"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Each one is unique,\nbut every time any sugar is consumed,", 
            "dur": "3.367", 
            "start": "267.537"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it kickstarts a domino effect in the brain\nthat sparks a rewarding feeling.", 
            "dur": "4.337", 
            "start": "270.928"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Too much, too often,\nand things can go into overdrive.", 
            "dur": "3.407", 
            "start": "275.289"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, yes, overconsumption of sugar\ncan have addictive effects on the brain,", 
            "dur": "4.231", 
            "start": "278.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but a wedge of cake once\nin a while won&#39;t hurt you.", 
            "dur": "3.203", 
            "start": "282.975"
        }
    ], 
